        setLoaded(false);
    }
    ...
```

Assess whether this comment identifies a genuine bug/correctness issue worth fixing, or whether it's a false positive / misunderstanding.

Specifically evaluate:
- Is "calling setState conditionally during render, gated on comparing a prop to a mirrored piece of state" the officially-documented React pattern for "adjusting state when a prop changes" (see React docs: "You Might Not Need an Effect" → "Adjusting some state when a prop changes")? If so, does it actually cause render loops in Strict Mode, or does the guard condition (`imageProps.src !== trackedSrc`) make it converge in one extra render, same as any other render-phase state update of this shape?
